                                <h3>Why  to have an Upper Back Lift at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston, Texas? </h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Many of our patients who have undergone massive weight loss or have developed excess back skin with age are very self-conscious about this area. They complain that clothes don’t fit correctly and are bothered by excess skin rolls. Patients also have problems with excess moisture under the skin which causes hygiene issues. Some patients simply desire a sleeker, tighter looking back in a dress or swimsuit. An Upper Back Lift can help you achieve this sleek contour and help you feel better about your arms in clothing and swimsuits.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Upper Back Lift procedures are often a careful balance between scarring and contour.  While everyone’s goal is to maximize contour and minimize scarring, sometimes a trade off must exist. At The Oaks Plastic Surgery we take care to place the scar behind the bra line brassiere.  The surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery want to work with you to achieve your specific goals.
                                </p>
